                <h1>Understanding Adverse Action: What You Need to Know</h1>
                <p>Adverse action refers to any unfavorable decision made by an individual or organization affecting an individual’s rights, opportunities, or status. This can include actions like denying employment or credit based on negative assessment. Understanding adverse actions is essential for ensuring fairness in decision-making processes.</p>
